text: Conventional lipoma is a type of lipoma characterized as a benign, well-circumscribed tumor composed of lobules of mature adipocytes. It arises within subcutaneous tissue, deep soft tissues, or on the surface of bones. Additionally, conventional lipoma is also known by its exact synonym, classic type lipoma.

Kidney lipoma is a type of kidney benign neoplasm and also a type of lipoma, which derives from some adipocyte. It is defined as a lipoma that is located in the kidney and has the exact synonym "Lipoma of kidney."

Pleural lipoma is a type of respiratory system benign neoplasm, pleural disease, and lipoma. It is classified as a condition that at least derives from adipocytes and has its location in the pleura. Pleural lipoma is defined as a respiratory system benign neoplasm that originates from fat cells and is situated in the pleura. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with Lipoma of Pleura.

Breast lipoma is a type of breast benign neoplasm, lipoma, and something that at least derives from some adipocyte. It has the definition of being a breast benign neoplasm that is composed of lipocytes. Additionally, it has the exact synonym "Lipoma of breast."

Chest wall lipoma is a type of thoracic benign neoplasm, a type of lipoma, and a type of something that at least derives from some adipocyte and has its location in the chest wall. It is defined as a thoracic benign neoplasm that derives from fat cells and is located in the chest wall. Additionally, it has an exact synonym: Lipoma of the Chest Wall.

Gallbladder lipoma is a type of gallbladder benign neoplasm and a kind of lipoma, which is a condition that at least derives from adipocytes and has its location in the gallbladder. It is defined as a gallbladder benign neoplasm that is located in the gallbladder and derives from fat cells. Additionally, gallbladder lipoma is exactly synonymous with Lipoma of the gallbladder.

External ear lipoma is a type of auditory system benign neoplasm, which is also a type of lipoma. This condition is derived at least in part from adipocytes and is categorized as a disease that is located within the external acoustic meatus. The definition of external ear lipoma is an auditory system benign neoplasm that is located in the external ear. It has exact synonyms including Lipoma of external auditory meatus, Lipoma of the External ear, and external auditory meatus lipoma.

Axillary lipoma is a type of thoracic benign neoplasm, a type of lipoma, and a type of something that at least derives from some adipocyte. It is defined as a thoracic benign neoplasm located in the axilla, an area directly under the arm and shoulder joint, composed of adipose tissue. Axillary lipoma is also exactly synonymous with Lipoma of axilla.

Lipoma of the spermatic cord is a type of benign neoplasm that occurs in the male reproductive organ and is specifically classified as a paratesticular lipoma. It is characterized by deriving at least partially from adipocytes and is associated with diseases located in the male reproductive system, particularly within the spermatic cord. The condition is defined as a paratesticular lipoma that is located in the spermatic cord and originates from fat cells. It is also exactly synonymous with Spermatic Cord Lipoma.

Paratesticular lipoma is a type of lipoma and a type of reproductive organ benign neoplasm. It is also a type of entity that at least derives from an adipocyte. It is defined as a reproductive organ benign neoplasm that derives from fat cells located in the paratesticular region.
Chondroid lipoma is a type of lipoma characterized as a deep-seated, firm, yellow tumor that typically occurs on the legs of women.

Extrahepatic bile duct lipoma is classified as a type of biliary tract benign neoplasm, lipoma, and bile duct disease. It originates from adipocytes and is located in the extrahepatic bile duct. Defined as a biliary tract benign neoplasm situated in the extrahepatic bile duct and deriving from fat cells, it is also exactly synonymous with Lipoma of the extrahepatic bile duct.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:cholelithiasis rdfs:subClassOf :gallbladder_disease .
text: cholelithiasis is a type of gallbladder disease.

Pinta disease is a primary bacterial infectious disease that is a type of condition transmitted at least by contact. It is defined as a disease resulting in infection located in the skin, with its material basis in Treponema carateum, which is transmitted by contact with the skin and mucous membrane of an infected person. The infection manifests symptoms such as a pruritic plaque, which slowly enlarges and becomes pigmented and hyperkeratotic.

Dermatomyositis is equivalent to an entity that intersects with something characterized by myositis and something that at least encompasses a disease located in a zone of the skin and something that at least encompasses a disease located in muscle tissue. It is classified as a type of skin disease and also as a type of myositis. Furthermore, dermatomyositis is recognized as a type of condition that invariably presents with the symptom of muscle weakness. It is defined as a form of myositis that leads to inflammation either in the muscle or in the skin, where a skin rash is frequently observed before the emergence of muscle weakness. This condition can stem from a viral infection or an autoimmune reaction. Dermatomyositis is precisely synonymous with Polymyositis with skin involvement and dermatopolymyositis. Additionally, it has related synonyms, including Amyopathic dermatomyositis, which is mentioned twice, indicating its significant association with the condition.

Borderline leprosy is a type of leprosy that is transmitted by some form of droplet spread transmission. It is defined as a leprosy resulting in small numerous red irregularly shaped plaques. Furthermore, borderline leprosy is also known by exact synonyms, including Borderline or dimorphous leprosy and Midborderline leprosy.
Aortic atherosclerosis is a type of atherosclerosis and is exactly synonymous with Atherosclerosis of aorta.
Histoplasmosis pericarditis, which is a type of pericarditis, has an exact synonym: Histoplasmosis with pericarditis.
Brown's tendon sheath syndrome is a type of mechanical strabismus, which is defined as a mechanical strabismus characterized by impairment of eye movements.

Exhibitionism is a type of paraphilia disorder, which is defined as a paraphilia disorder characterized by recurrent sexual urges, fantasies, or behaviors involving the exposure of one's genitals to an unsuspecting stranger.

Leprosy is a primary bacterial infectious disease with a material basis in Mycobacterium leprae. It is transmitted by droplet spread transmission, specifically by aerosol spread from infected nasal secretions to exposed nasal and oral mucosa. The disease primarily affects the superficial peripheral nerves, skin, mucous membranes of the upper respiratory tract, the anterior chamber of the eyes, and the testes. Common symptoms of leprosy include skin lesions, sensory loss, motor loss, and eye damage. Additionally, the disease is known to have locations in the peripheral nervous system, testis, eye, and upper respiratory tract.

Thalassemia is a type of autosomal recessive disease, hemolytic anemia, and something that at least has a material basis in some autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined as a hemolytic anemia characterized by decreased synthesis of one or more hemoglobin polypeptide chains. Furthermore, thalassemia has exact synonyms including Sickle-cell thalassemia with crisis, Sickle-cell thalassemia without crisis, thalassemia Hb-S disease with crisis, and thalassemia Hb-S disease without crisis.

Ehrlichiosis, also known as human ehrlichiosis and precisely matched with MESH:D016873, is defined as a primary bacterial infectious disease. This condition results from an infection located in leukocytes, with a material basis in either Ehrlichia chaffeensis or Anaplasma phagocytophilum. These bacteria are transmitted by the lone star tick and the black-legged tick, respectively. Symptoms of ehrlichiosis include headache, muscle aches, fatigue, and rash.
Pleurisy is a type of pleural disease, defined as a pleural disease characterized by inflammation of the pleura, which is the lining of the pleural cavity surrounding the lungs.

Tuberculoid leprosy is a type of leprosy that is transmitted by some form of droplet spread transmission. It is defined as a leprosy that results in one erythematous large plaque with well-defined borders that are elevated and slope down into an atrophic center. Additionally, tuberculoid leprosy is exactly synonymous with Smooth leprosy and type T leprosy.

Louping ill is a type of viral infectious disease that is characterized by having a material basis in the Louping ill virus and is transmitted by the Ixodes ricinus, commonly known as the sheep tick. This disease manifests symptoms such as lethargy, fever, and muscle pain. Additionally, louping ill is defined as a viral infectious disease that results in infection primarily in sheep and, on rare occasions, in humans. It is caused by the Louping ill virus, which is transmitted by the sheep tick, Ixodes ricinus. The infection is marked by symptoms including lethargy, muscle pains, fever, and focal neurological signs.
Strawberry gallbladder is a type of gallbladder disease, which is exactly synonymous with Cholesterolosis of the gallbladder.
Otorrhea is a type of auditory system disease characterized by the discharge or drainage of fluid from the ear, and it is also known as discharging ear.

Mumps is defined as a viral infectious disease characterized by inflammation located in a salivary gland. This condition is synonymous with being a disease that intersects with both viral infectious diseases and diseases located in some saliva secreting glands. Additionally, mumps falls under the category of salivary gland diseases, herpangina, and diseases that have a material basis in mumps orthorubulavirus. It is also classified as a disease that is transmitted through either droplet spread transmission or vehicle-borne fomite transmission. The symptoms associated with mumps include tiredness, loss of appetite, headache, and fever. The disease is caused by the Mumps rubulavirus, which can be transmitted by droplet spread of saliva or mucus from the mouth, nose, or throat of an infected person, or by contaminated fomites. The infection leads to symptoms such as fever, headache, muscle aches, tiredness, loss of appetite, and swollen and tender salivary glands under the ears or jaw on one or both sides of the face.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:subendocardial_infarction_acute_myocardial_infarction rdfs:subClassOf :acute_myocardial_infarction .
text: subendocardial infarction acute myocardial infarction is a type of acute myocardial infarction.
Left bundle branch hemiblock, which is a type of heart conduction disease, is exactly synonymous with Left bundle branch block.

Heart conduction disease is a type of heart disease and is defined as a cardiovascular system disease that involves the heart's electrical conduction system. It is also exactly synonymous with heart rhythm disease.

Prostate cancer is defined as a male reproductive organ cancer located in the prostate gland, which is the same as something that intersects between something that is cancer and something that is at least a disease with a location in the prostate gland. It is a type of male reproductive organ cancer as well as a type of prostate disease. Prostate cancer is identified by several exact synonyms including NGP - new growth of prostate, hereditary prostate cancer, malignant tumor of the prostate, prostate cancer, familial, prostate neoplasm, prostatic cancer, prostatic neoplasm, and tumor of the prostate.

Prostate carcinoma is a type of prostate cancer and also a type of carcinoma, which is characterized by abnormally proliferating cells that derive from epithelial cells. This type of cancer originates from cells at least derived from some epithelial cell and is located in the prostate gland. Prostate carcinoma is defined as a prostate cancer with a material basis in cells that abnormally proliferate deriving from epithelial cells. Additionally, "cancer of the prostate" and "carcinoma of the prostate" are exact synonyms for prostate carcinoma.

Prostate squamous cell carcinoma is a type of prostate carcinoma and a type of squamous cell carcinoma, which is a type of something that at least derives from some squamous epithelial cell. It is defined as a squamous cell carcinoma that is located in the prostate.

Prostate malignant phyllodes tumor is a type of prostate cancer and it is precisely synonymous with malignant Phyllodes neoplasm of the prostate. This prostate cancer is defined by the presence of glandular elements and a cellular stroma that exhibits mitotic activity and nuclear atypia, arising from the prostate gland.

Familial periodic paralysis is a type of metal metabolism disorder characterized by episodes of muscle paralysis during which the affected muscles become flaccid and the deep tendon reflexes disappear. Between these episodes, the affected muscles usually work normally. This disorder is caused by mutations in genes involved in the sodium and calcium channels in nerve cells.

Prostate lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and also a type of prostate cancer, specifically a prostate cancer that affects lymphocytes and arises from the prostate gland. This condition has a material basis in some lymphocyte. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with lymphoma of the prostate.
Monocular esotropia, a type of esotropia, is defined as an esotropia characterized by excessive convergence of the visual axes, leading to a cross-eye appearance.

Raynaud disease is a type of peripheral vascular disease and is defined as a peripheral vascular disease characterized by bilateral Raynaud phenomenon, which is the abrupt onset of digital paleness or cyanosis in response to cold exposure or stress. It has exact synonyms, including Raynaud's disease and Raynaud's syndrome. Moreover, Raynaud disease has an exact match with MESH:D011928.

Parotitis is a type of parotid disease and is characterized by the inflammation of one or both parotid glands. It is a condition that falls under the category of diseases with at least the symptom of some inflammation. Furthermore, Parotitis has an exact match with the MESH code D010309.

Parotid disease is equivalent to a condition that intersects with both a disease and something that, at a minimum, involves the parotid gland as its location. Furthermore, parotid disease falls under the category of salivary gland diseases. It is defined as a salivary gland disease specifically located in the parotid gland.
Sialadenitis is a type of salivary gland disease and is defined as a salivary gland disease characterized as an infection of the salivary glands. It also has the exact synonym Sialoadenitis.

Viral meningitis is a type of viral infectious disease and a type of meningitis, which at least has a material basis in some viruses. It is defined as a meningitis that has a material basis in a viral infection.

Endocarditis is a type of endocardium disease and is characterized by inflammation of the endocardium of the heart chambers and valves. It is also a condition that involves some inflammation, indicating that it falls under diseases that exhibit this symptom.

Pneumoconiosis is a type of interstitial lung disease and is characterized by an abnormal pulmonary interstitial morphology. It is transmitted through airborne transmission. Furthermore, pneumoconiosis is defined as an interstitial lung disease that is caused by the inhalation of dust.
Mixed mineral dust pneumoconiosis is a type of pneumoconiosis, which is defined as a pneumoconiosis caused by the inhalation of mixed mineral dust particles.
Asbestosis is a type of pneumoconiosis, defined as a pneumoconiosis caused by the inhalation and retention of asbestos fibers.

Baritosis is a type of pneumoconiosis and is defined as a pneumoconiosis characterized by the formation of fine dense lesions in the lung parenchyma, caused by long-standing exposure to barium dust. The lesions do not affect the lung function and disappear without treatment after the exposure to barium dust stops.

Berylliosis is a type of respiratory allergy and a type of pneumoconiosis. It is characterized by having at least some allergic reaction as a symptom and involves the respiratory tract as the location of the disease. The condition is defined as a pneumoconiosis that involves an allergic response located in the lungs, caused by the inhalation of beryllium compounds. Additionally, berylliosis is also known by its exact synonym, beryllium poisoning.

Byssinosis is a type of pneumoconiosis and also falls under the category of conditions that at least have the symptom of some chest tightness. It is defined as a pneumoconiosis characterized by a hypersensitive reaction to inhaled dust during the initial processing of cotton, flax, or hemp, with symptoms including chest tightness, cough, and wheezing. Byssinosis is exactly synonymous with Flax-dressers' disease, Stripper's asthma, and cotton mill fever.

Anthracosilicosis is a type of pneumoconiosis, defined as a pneumoconiosis characterized by fibrosis of the lung parenchyma caused by inhalation of carbon and silica dust. It manifests as shortness of breath and induces fibrous nodule formation in the lung.

Silicosis is a type of pneumoconiosis, defined as a pneumoconiosis that is an inflammation and scarring of the upper lobes of the lungs causing nodular lesions resulting from the inhalation of silica, quartz, or slate particles. It is exactly synonymous with several terms, including Pneumoconiosis due to silicates, Silica pneumoconiosis, Silicotic fibrosis of lung, and silicotuberculosis.

Caplan's syndrome is a type of pneumoconiosis and is defined as a pneumoconiosis that occurs in humans who also have rheumatoid arthritis. It is exactly synonymous with Caplan syndrome, Caplan's disease, Caplans syndrome, and Rheumatoid pneumoconiosis.

Anthracosis is a type of pneumoconiosis, which is characterized by the deposition of carbon or coal dust in the lung parenchyma, leading to the formation of black nodules and emphysema. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Coal Miner's Pneumoconiosis, Coal workers' lung, Coal workers' pneumoconiosis, Melanoedema, and black lung.

Siderosis is a type of pneumoconiosis and has the definition of being a pneumoconiosis that is characterized by the deposition of excess iron in body tissue resulting from the inhalation of iron in the mining dust or welding fumes. It also has the exact synonym pulmonary siderosis.

Pulmonary talcosis is a type of pneumoconiosis characterized by fibrosis and granulomatous changes in the lung parenchyma, resulting from exposure to talc. It is also exactly synonymous with pneumoconiosis due to talc, talc pneumoconiosis, and talcosis.
Slate pneumoconiosis is a type of pneumoconiosis, which is defined as a pneumoconiosis that is caused by exposure to slate dust. It also has the exact synonym Schistosis.
Kaolin pneumoconiosis is a type of pneumoconiosis and it is defined as a pneumoconiosis that is caused by inhalation of kaolin dust. It also has an exact synonym, Kaolinosis.

Glaucomatous atrophy of the optic disc is a specific type of optic atrophy, which is defined as an optic atrophy characterized by optic nerve damage. This damage comes with an increased optic cup to disc ratio secondary to glaucoma. Glaucoma is an eye disease associated with abnormal aqueous fluid outflow that inappropriately raises intraocular pressure, leading to optic nerve atrophy with progressive visual field loss. Glaucomatous atrophy of the optic disc can be caused by any form of glaucoma. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with Glaucomatous atrophy [cupping] of the optic disc.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chronic_meningitis rdfs:subClassOf :meningitis .
text: chronic meningitis is a type of meningitis.

Blepharophimosis is a type of physical disorder and a specific kind of eyelid disease. It is a condition that arises from some abnormality of prenatal development or birth. Blepharophimosis is defined as an eyelid disease characterized by abnormal narrowness of the palpebral fissure in the horizontal direction due to the lateral displacement of the medial canthi of the eyelids. Additionally, blepharophimosis corresponds exactly to MESH:D016569.

A solitary cyst of the breast is a type of breast cyst that is defined as a breast cyst characterized by a single, fluid-filled cyst in the breast parenchyma. It is also exactly synonymous with Solitary Cyst of the breast.

Aggressive NK cell leukemia is a specific type of leukemia that is also categorized under cell type cancer. It is defined as a leukemia characterized by the systemic proliferation of NK cells, which is closely associated with the Epstein-Barr virus and is found in the peripheral blood, bone marrow, liver, and spleen. This condition is synonymous with aggressive NK-cell leukaemia, large granular lymphocyte leukemia of the NK-cell type, natural killer cell leukaemia, and natural killer cell leukemia. Moreover, it is described as an intersection of leukemia and entities that derive from some natural killer cell, emphasizing its origin from natural killer cells.
A breast cyst, which is a type of breast benign neoplasm, is characterized by a fluid-filled sac. It is also exactly synonymous with "Cyst of the breast."

Breast fibroadenosis is a type of breast benign neoplasm characterized by having a material basis in fibrous and epithelial tissue, where tumor cells form glands or gland-like structures. It is exactly synonymous with Fibroadenosis - breast and Fibroadenosis of breast.

Fibrosclerosis of the breast is a type of non-proliferative fibrocystic change of the breast, which is defined as a non-proliferative fibrocystic change of the breast that contains scar tissue. It also has an exact synonym, namely Fibrosis of the breast.

Breast fibrocystic disease is a type of breast benign neoplasm and has a definition as a breast benign neoplasm that has a material basis in fibrous tissue and is characterized by the development of cystic spaces. It has exact synonyms such as Diffuse cystic mastopathy, Fibrocystic disease of breast, and Breast Fibrocystic Change.
Chronic leukemia is a type of leukemia characterized by a slow development. It is synonymously related to CLL, CML, and adult chronic leukemia.

Eosinophilic meningitis is a type of chronic meningitis characterized by the presence of 10 or more eosinophils/microL in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) or a CSF eosinophilia of at least 10 percent. This condition exhibits symptoms ranging from mild to severe headaches, dizziness, nausea, vomiting, fever, neck stiffness, paresthesia, and stabbing pain in the trunk and limbs that is aggravated by touch. Additionally, eosinophilic meningitis is identified by symptoms such as paresthesia and dizziness.

Epididymis cancer is defined as a type of cancer that intersects with diseases located specifically in the epididymis, making it a subtype of both epididymis diseases and male reproductive organ cancers. It is precisely characterized as a male reproductive organ cancer situated in the epididymis. Furthermore, epididymis cancer is exactly synonymous with malignant epididymal tumor, malignant neoplasm of epididymis, and malignant tumor of epididymis.

Epididymis adenocarcinoma is a type of cancer that occurs in the epididymis and is also classified as a type of adenocarcinoma. This specific cancer is characterized as a subtype of epididymis cancer that originates from epithelial cells of glandular origin. It is defined as an epididymis cancer that derives from epithelial cells of glandular origin, highlighting its basis in cells that are part of the epithelium and have a glandular origin. Additionally, epididymis adenocarcinoma is related to and synonymously referred to as adenocarcinoma of the epididymis.

Lymphoid leukemia is a type of leukemia defined as a leukemia that has a material basis in a B-cell or T-cell lineage, involving primarily the bone marrow and the peripheral blood. It is also exactly known as lymphoblastic leukaemia, lymphoblastic leukemia, and lymphocytic leukaemia.

Yaws is a primary bacterial infectious disease transmitted through direct skin contact with an infected person. This disease results in infections located in the skin, joints, or bones and is caused by Treponema pallidum subsp. pertenue. It is characterized by symptoms such as skin lesions. Furthermore, the disease can manifest in various locations, including the skin, bones, and articulations. Yaws is also known by several exact synonyms, including Bouba, frambesia, frambesia tropica, frambosie, polypapilloma tropicum, and thymosis.

Strabismic amblyopia is a type of amblyopia that is characterized by strabismus or eye misalignment, where the brain begins to ignore the eye that is not straight, subsequently causing the vision to drop in that eye. It is also exactly known as suppression amblyopia.

Amblyopia is a type of eye disease, which is defined as an eye disease characterized by poor vision in one eye resulting from the brain's failure to process inputs from one eye and over time favors the other eye. The weaker or lazy eye often wanders inward or outward. It has an exact synonym, "lazy eye," and an exact match in the MESH database with the identifier D000550.

Refractive amblyopia is a type of amblyopia that is characterized by refractive error in one or both eyes, which, if not corrected early in childhood, results in poor development of the visual function in the affected eye(s). It is also precisely known as ametropic amblyopia.

Deprivation amblyopia is a type of amblyopia characterized by a structural anomaly that impairs vision, such as a droopy eyelid or an opacity in the eye, including conditions like a cataract or corneal scar. It is also exactly synonymous with disuse amblyopia.

Amyotrophic neuralgia, which has the exact synonym neuralgic amyotrophy, is a type of autosomal dominant disease and brachial plexus neuropathy. It is characterized by a condition that at least has a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. Specifically, amyotrophic neuralgia is defined as a brachial plexus neuropathy that is characterized by acute, recurrent episodes of brachial plexus neuropathy with muscle weakness and atrophy preceded by severe pain in the affected arm. This condition has its material basis in a heterozygous mutation in the SEPT9 gene on chromosome 17q25.

Prolymphocytic leukemia is a type of chronic lymphocytic leukemia, which is defined as a chronic lymphocytic leukemia characterized by the presence of medium-sized lymphocytes with visible nucleoli (prolymphocytes) in the peripheral blood, bone marrow, and spleen. It has exact synonyms such as PLL and Prolymphocytic leukaemia.

Secondary hypertrophic osteoarthropathy is a type of arthropathy, which is exactly synonymous with Bamberger-Marie disease, HPOA - hypertrophic pulmonary osteoarthropathy, Marie Bamberger disease, and hypertrophic pulmonary osteoarthropathy.

Pneumonic plague is a type of plague and a lung disease that can be transmitted by flea-borne transmission. It manifests symptoms such as fever, cough, breathing problems, and chills. The disease specifically affects the lungs. Pneumonic plague is defined as a plague resulting in an infection located in the lung, which results from the direct inhalation of the bacillus, and is characterized by symptoms including fever, chills, cough, and difficulty breathing. Additionally, pneumonic plague is also known by its exact synonyms: primary pneumonic plague and secondary pneumonic plague.
Seminal vesicle chronic gonorrhea, which is a type of gonococcal seminal vesiculitis, is exactly synonymous with Gonococcal seminal vesiculitis, chronic.

Bacterial infectious disease is the same as something that is both a disease and has at least a material basis in some bacteria. It is a type of disease caused by an infectious agent. Furthermore, a bacterial infectious disease is defined as a disease caused by an infectious agent that results in infection and has a material basis in bacteria.

Chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) is a type of lymphoma, specifically a type of lymphoid leukemia. It is characterized by a condition that fundamentally has a material basis in some lymphocytes of B lineage. CLL is defined as a lymphocytic leukemia characterized by the overproduction of B-cells and their accumulation in the bone marrow and blood. It is also known by several exact synonyms: B-cell chronic lymphocytic leukemia, B-cell chronic lymphocytic leukaemia, chronic lymphatic leukemia, chronic lymphatic leukaemia, chronic lymphocytic leukaemia, lymphoplasmacytic leukemia, and lymphoplasmacytic leukaemia. Additionally, CLL has a related synonym: B-cell chronic lymphoid leukemia.

Gonococcal seminal vesiculitis is the same as something that is at the intersection of gonorrhea and a disease that has its location in the seminal vesicle. It is a type of gonorrhea as well as a type of vesiculitis. Moreover, Gonococcal seminal vesiculitis has an exact synonym, which is Gonorrhea of the seminal vesicle.
Acute pericementitis is a type of periodontitis and has an exact synonym, acute periodontitis.

Klippel Feil Syndrome is a type of spinal disease, physical disorder, and syndrome. It is characterized by an intersection of a physical disorder and an intersection of diseases that have symptoms based in the vertebral column. It is defined as a physical disorder characterized by abnormal segmentation of the vertebra during fetal development, resulting in the fusion located in the cervical vertebra. Klippel Feil Syndrome has exact synonyms, including Klippel-Feil and Turner syndrome, Klippel-Feil deformity, deafness and facial asymmetry, autosomal dominant Klippel-Feil syndrome, congenital dystrophia brevicollis, and congenital synostosis of cervical vertebrae.
Stable condition keratoconus is a type of keratoconus and has an exact synonym: Keratoconus, stable condition.
Purulent acute otitis media is a type of suppurative otitis media, defined as a suppurative otitis media with sudden onset and a short course.

Mooren's ulcer is a type of corneal ulcer and is also known as Mooren ulcer. It is a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some inflammation. Moreover, Mooren's ulcer is defined as a corneal ulcer that is characterized by painful peripheral corneal ulceration, sterile limbal inflammation, and episcleral and conjunctival edema.

A mycotic corneal ulcer is a type of corneal ulcer defined as a corneal ulcer characterized by ulceration of the cornea secondary to fungal infection. It is caused by minor trauma and subsequent infection by mycotic organisms, including Candida, Aspergillus, Fusarium, and Rhizopus.
A marginal corneal ulcer is a type of corneal ulcer that is defined as a corneal ulcer characterized by infiltrate formation in the marginal zone that is parallel but separated from the limbus.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:hypopyon_ulcer rdfs:subClassOf :hypopyon .
text: hypopyon ulcer is a type of hypopyon.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:hypopyon rdfs:subClassOf :iridocyclitis .
text: hypopyon is a type of iridocyclitis.
A ring corneal ulcer, which is a type of corneal ulcer, is defined as a corneal ulcer characterized by a ring of infiltration and/or ulceration that forms on the cornea.

A perforated corneal ulcer, which is a specific type of corneal ulcer, is defined as a corneal ulcer that has progressed and thinned the cornea to the extent that the cornea ruptures, creating a small hole that may drain or appear to contain pigment.

Tonsillitis is defined as an upper respiratory tract disease characterized by inflammation of the tonsils due to bacterial (Group A streptococcus) and viral (Epstein-Barr virus, adenovirus) infections. This condition manifests through various symptoms including severe sore throat, painful or difficult swallowing (dysphagia), coughing, headache, myalgia, fever, and chills. Additionally, tonsillitis is associated with a phenotype that includes some abnormality of the tonsils and other symptoms such as inflammation of the pharynx. It is also known by the exact synonyms "throat infection - tonsillitis" and "chronic tonsillitis."

Legionnaires' disease is a type of legionellosis characterized by a severe form of infection producing pneumonia, with symptoms including fever, chills, and cough. It is transmitted at least partially through droplet spread and has features of pneumonia. Legionnaires' disease is also known by exact synonyms such as Infection by Legionella pneumophila, Legionella, Legionella pneumonia, and Legionnaire's disease.

Legionellosis is a primary bacterial infectious disease, also known exactly as Legionella infection. It results in an infection located in the respiratory tract and has a material basis in Legionella pneumophila. This disease is transmitted by the inhalation of droplets containing the bacteria. The symptoms of legionellosis include dry cough, fever, headache, and diarrhea.

Common cold is a type of upper respiratory tract disease characterized by inflammation of the mucous membranes of the nose, throat, eyes, and eustachian tubes, leading to watery then purulent discharge. It is an acute contagious disease caused by a range of viruses including rhinoviruses, human parainfluenza viruses, human respiratory syncytial virus, influenza viruses, adenoviruses, enteroviruses, or metapneumovirus. The common cold is also known by several exact synonyms, including Acute viral rhinopharyngitis, Nasopharyngitis - acute, acute coryza, acute nasopharyngitis, acute rhinitis, and rhino-sinusitis.
Nasopharyngitis is a type of nasopharyngeal disease characterized by inflammation of the nasal passages and the upper part of the pharynx. It is also precisely known as chronic nasopharyngitis.
Dentin caries is a type of dental caries and has exact synonyms such as Compound dental caries and Dental caries extending into dentine.
Patellar tendinitis is a type of tendinitis, which is exactly synonymous with Patellar tendonitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:diaphragmatic_eventration rdfs:subClassOf :diaphragm_disease .
text: diaphragmatic eventration is a type of diaphragm disease.

Diaphragm disease is the same as something that is both a disease and is located in the diaphragm. It is a type of muscular disease. Furthermore, diaphragm disease is defined as a muscular disease that is located in the diaphragm.

Esophageal atresia is a type of esophageal disease and has exact synonyms such as Congenital atresia of the esophagus, Congenital imperforate esophagus, Imperforate esophagus, and Oesophageal atresia.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:intestinal_atresia rdfs:subClassOf :intestinal_disease .
text: intestinal atresia is a type of intestinal disease.

Hirschsprung's disease is a type of megacolon, characterized by a blockage of the large intestine due to improper muscle movement in the bowel. It is exactly synonymous with several terms, including Hirschsprung disease, aganglionic megacolon, congenital megacolon, macrocolon, pelvirectal achalasia, and total intestinal aganglionosis.

Imperforate anus is defined as a condition that intersects with both a physical disorder and a disease that specifically affects the anus. It is categorized as a type of physical disorder as well as a type of anus disease. Furthermore, imperforate anus is exactly synonymous with Congenital atresia of anus, Congenital or infantile occlusion of anus, and anal atresia.
Adrenal cortical hypofunction is a type of adrenal cortex disease, which has exact synonyms Adrenal Cortical Insufficiency and Corticoadrenal Insufficiency.
Orbital granuloma is a type of chronic orbital inflammation and is characterized by having at least some phenotype of granuloma.

Dressler's syndrome is a type of pericarditis characterized by inflammation occurring after injury and is located in the pericardium. It has exact synonyms, including Dressler syndrome and Postmyocardial infarction syndrome.

Malignant otitis externa is a type of otitis externa defined as an otitis externa involving infection of the external ear that has spread to involve the skull bone containing part of the ear canal, the middle ear, and the inner ear. It is caused by the bacteria Pseudomonas and is common in people with weakened immune systems and in older people with diabetes.

Beach ear, a type of otitis externa, is defined as a microbial infection that occurs suddenly, rapidly worsens, and becomes very painful and alarming. It is caused by swimming in polluted water, scratching the ear or inside the ear, and objects stuck in the ear. Occasionally, it is associated with a middle ear infection or upper respiratory infections such as colds. Beach ear is also known by exact synonyms including Tank ear, acute bacterial inflammation of the external ear, acute otitis externa, diffuse, acute swimmer's ear, and acute swimmers' ear.

Chronic fungal otitis externa is a type of otomycosis, a fungal infectious disease, and something that at least has a material basis in some fungi. It is defined as an otomycosis that is persistent, long-lasting, or recurrent. Additionally, chronic fungal otitis externa has an exact synonym: chronic mycotic otitis externa.

An acute infection of the pinna is a type of otitis externa, defined as an otitis externa that involves bacterial infections often related to underlying comorbidities as well as trauma. Trauma sources commonly include ear piercing, boxing, blunt trauma, burns, bite wounds, and iatrogenic insults. The common bacterial pathogens associated with this condition are staphylococcal and streptococcal species.

Double pterygium is a specific type of pterygium characterized by a fleshy outpouching of conjunctival growth that appears to have multiple heads or areas of bulk or origin. It is distinguished by having symptoms such as multiple fleshy bumps on the surface of the eye, a foreign body sensation, decreased vision, and astigmatism. This condition is more common in individuals prone to ocular surface injury, particularly those living in sunny, hot, and dry climates, and it progresses from pinguecula. Additionally, double pterygium is associated with at least having some loss of vision and features some degree of astigmatism as part of its disease manifestation.

Conjunctival pterygium is a type of pterygium and also a type of conjunctival disease. It is characterized by conjunctival degeneration, a fleshy outpouching of conjunctival growth, and exhibits symptoms such as fleshy bumps on the surface of the eye, foreign body sensation, decreased vision, and astigmatism. These pterygiums are more common in people prone to ocular surface injury, such as those living in sunny, hot, and dry climates, and they progress from pinguecula. Additionally, conjunctival pterygium is associated with symptoms like loss of vision and conjunctival degeneration. It is linked with diseases that are located in the conjunctiva and diseases that feature astigmatism. Conjunctival pterygium is also known by its exact synonym, "Web eye."

Viral pneumonia is a type of pneumonia, which is a category of viral infectious diseases. It is characterized by having a material basis in various viruses, including but not limited to influenza virus, parainfluenza, adenovirus, rhinovirus, herpes simplex virus, respiratory syncytial virus, hantavirus, and cytomegalovirus. This condition specifically affects the lungs and features pneumonia, an inflammatory illness of the lung. Viral pneumonia is defined as a pneumonia described as an inflammatory illness of the lung commonly caused by the aforementioned viruses.

Stomach cancer, also known as gastric cancer or gastric neoplasm, is defined as a gastrointestinal system cancer that is located in the stomach. It falls under the category of both stomach disease and gastrointestinal system cancer. This condition is essentially the intersection of cancer and diseases that are located in the stomach.

Malignant gastric granular cell tumor is a type of stomach cancer and it has several exact synonyms. These include malignant gastric granular cell tumour, malignant granular cell tumor of the stomach, and malignant granular cell tumour of the stomach.

Gastric fundus cancer is identical to a condition that falls at the intersection of cancer and diseases located in the fundus of the stomach. It is a specific type of stomach cancer characterized by its location in the gastric fundus. Gastric fundus cancer is defined as a stomach cancer located in the gastric fundus. Furthermore, it has exact synonyms, including Ca fundus - stomach, malignant neoplasm of fundus of stomach, and malignant tumor of fundus of stomach.

Gastric lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and a type of stomach cancer, which is characterized by having a material basis in lymphocytes. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with Lymphoma of the stomach.
Microinvasive gastric cancer, which is a type of gastric adenocarcinoma, is also exactly synonymous with surface gastric cancer and early gastric cancer.

Pylorus cancer is equivalent to an intersection of entities that are both cancer and diseases located at the pylorus. It is a specific type of stomach cancer. Additionally, pylorus cancer is exactly synonymous with several terms, including "Ca pylorus - stomach," "malignant neoplasm of Prepylorus," "malignant neoplasm of pylorus of stomach," and "malignant tumor of pylorus."

Pyloric antrum cancer is equivalent to a type of cancer that intersects with a condition classified as a disease, which is located in the pyloric antrum. It is a specific type of pylorus cancer. Moreover, pyloric antrum cancer is exactly synonymous with malignant neoplasm of the antrum of the stomach and malignant tumor of the pyloric antrum.

Cardia cancer, which is a type of stomach cancer, is defined as a cancer located in the gastric cardia. It is the same as something that intersects with something that is a cancer and something that is at least a disease with a location in some cardia of the stomach. Furthermore, cardia cancer has exact synonyms, including "Ca cardia - stomach" and "malignant neoplasm of cardia of stomach."
Acute eustachian salpingitis is a type of otosalpingitis, which is defined as otosalpingitis with a sudden onset and a short course. It also has the exact synonym "acute eustachian tube salpingitis."
Meningoencephalitis is a type of central nervous system disease characterized by a condition that involves encephalitis occurring alongside meningitis.

Supine hypotensive syndrome is identified as a type of vascular disease and is also associated with symptoms such as shock and vascular alterations. It is defined as a vascular disease characterized by severe supine hypotension in late pregnancy, which can lead to clinical presentations varying from minimal cardiovascular alterations to severe shock, due to the compression of the inferior vena cava by the gravid uterus. Additionally, supine hypotensive syndrome is precisely synonymous with both antepartum maternal hypotension syndrome and postpartum maternal hypotension syndrome.

Oculocerebrorenal syndrome, also known exactly as Lowe syndrome, Lowe oculocerebrorenal syndrome, and oculocerebrorenal syndrome of Lowe, is a type of syndrome and a specific form of X-linked recessive disease. It is characterized by a syndrome that has a material basis in mutation in the OCRL gene located on chromosome Xq26. The syndrome is distinguished by features including hydrophthalmia, cataract, mental retardation, vitamin D-resistant rickets, amino aciduria, and reduced ammonia production by the kidney. Moreover, it is a type of condition that inherently has a material basis in some form of X-linked recessive inheritance.

Late yaws is a type of yaws characterized by a condition that appears after five years of the initial infection, leading to disabling consequences on the nose, bones, and causing palmar/plantar hyperkeratosis. It is also known by several exact synonyms including Gummata and ulcers due to yaws, Gummata of yaws, Ulcers of yaws, Yaws gummata and ulcers, gummatous frambeside, multiple papillomata due to yaws and wet crab yaws, as well as nodular late yaws.

Early yaws, a type of yaws, is defined as a form of the disease characterized by an initial papule at the site of entry of the bacteria, which, without treatment, is followed by disseminated skin lesions across the body. It may also lead to bone pain and bone lesions. This condition is precisely referred to by various synonyms, including Frambesia, initial or primary; Initial frambesial ulcer; Initial lesions of yaws; Bone and joint lesions due to yaws; Bone and joint yaws lesion; Chancre of yaws; and Primary frambesia.

Osteomalacia is a type of bone remodeling disease and is defined as a bone remodeling disease that has a material basis in a vitamin D deficiency, resulting in softening located in the bone. Furthermore, osteomalacia has an exact match with MESH:D010018.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:calcium_metabolism_disease rdfs:subClassOf :mineral_metabolism_disease .
text: calcium metabolism disease is a type of mineral metabolism disease.
Leukodystrophy is a type of cerebral degeneration characterized by dysfunction of the white matter of the brain. It is a disease located in the cerebrum.

Metachromatic leukodystrophy is a type of sphingolipidosis characterized by the accumulation of sulfatides in cells, notably in the myelin-producing cells of the nervous system. It is precisely synonymous with MLD, Scholz cerebral sclerosis, arylsulfatase A deficiency, deficiency of cerebroside-sulfatase, and sulfatide lipoidosis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:refsum_disease rdfs:subClassOf :lipid_metabolism_disorder ;
    :has_definition "A lipid metabolic disorder that is characterized by a tetrad of clinical abnormalities: retinitis pigmentosa, peripheral neuropathy, cerebellar ataxia, and accumulation of an unusual branched-chain fatty acid, phytanic acid, in blood and tissues." ;
    :has_exact_synonym "Heredopathia atactica polyneuritiformis",
        "adult Refsum disease",
        "classic Refsum disease",
        "phytanic acid oxidase deficiency",
        "HMSN type IV"@en,
        "HSMN IV"@en,
        "Heredopathia atactica polyneuritiformis"@en,
        "Refsum's disease"@en .
text: Refsum disease is a type of lipid metabolism disorder characterized by a tetrad of clinical abnormalities: retinitis pigmentosa, peripheral neuropathy, cerebellar ataxia, and the accumulation of an unusual branched-chain fatty acid, phytanic acid, in blood and tissues. It has several exact synonyms, including HMSN type IV, HSMN IV, Heredopathia atactica polyneuritiformis (listed twice), Refsum's disease, adult Refsum disease, classic Refsum disease, and phytanic acid oxidase deficiency.

Retinitis pigmentosa is a type of retinal degeneration and is defined as a retinal degeneration characterized by the gradual deterioration of the photoreceptors or the retinal pigment epithelium of the retina leading to progressive sight loss. It also has the exact synonym "pericentral pigmentary retinopathy."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:krabbe_disease rdfs:subClassOf :sphingolipidosis ;
    :has_exact_synonym "Diffuse globoid body sclerosis"@en,
        "GLOBOID CELL LEUKOENCEPHALOPATHY"@en,
        "Galactosylceramide beta-galactosidase deficiency"@en,
        "Krabbe's disease"@en,
        "Krabbe's leukodystrophy"@en,
        "beta galactocerebrosidase deficiency"@en,
        "globoid cell leukodystrophy"@en .
text: Krabbe disease, a type of sphingolipidosis, is alternatively known by several exact synonyms. These include Diffuse Globoid Body Sclerosis, Globoid Cell Leukoencephalopathy, Galactosylceramide Beta-Galactosidase Deficiency, Krabbe's Disease, Krabbe's Leukodystrophy, Beta Galactocerebrosidase Deficiency, and Globoid Cell Leukodystrophy.

Adrenoleukodystrophy is a type of leukodystrophy and an X-linked recessive disease, which also has a material basis in X-linked recessive inheritance. It is defined as a leukodystrophy that disrupts the breakdown of very-long-chain fatty acids, leading to progressive brain damage, failure of the adrenal glands, and eventually death. Adrenoleukodystrophy is exactly synonymous with ALD, Bronze Schilder disease, Encephalitis periaxialis concentrica, Encephalitis periaxialis, Schilder's, Siemerling-Creutzfeldt Disease, X-linked adrenoleukodystrophy, diffuse sclerosis, and sudanophilic cerebral sclerosis. Furthermore, adrenoleukodystrophy has an exact match in the MESH database with the identifier D000326.

Intellectual disability is a type of specific developmental disorder that involves significant limitations in both mental functioning and adaptive behavior, including aspects such as communication, self-care, and social skills. It is also related to the synonym "mental retardation."

Mild pre-eclampsia is a type of pre-eclampsia defined as a condition characterized by the presence of hypertension without evidence of end-organ damage, in a woman who was normotensive before 20 weeks' gestation.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pre_eclampsia rdfs:subClassOf :hypertension ;
    :has_definition "A hypertension occurring during pregnancy characterized by large amounts of protein in the urine (proteinuria) and edema, usually by the last trimester of pregnancy." ;
    :has_exact_synonym "gestational hypertension"@en,
        "hypertension induced by pregnancy"@en,
        "pre-eclamptic toxaemia"@en,
        "preeclampsia"@en,
        "preeclampsia/eclampsia"@en,
        "pregnancy associated hypertension"@en,
        "pregnancy toxemia"@en,
        "proteinuric hypertension of pregnancy"@en,
        "toxaemia of pregnancy"@en .
text: Pre eclampsia is a type of hypertension and has a definition as a hypertension occurring during pregnancy characterized by large amounts of protein in the urine (proteinuria) and edema, usually by the last trimester of pregnancy. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including gestational hypertension, hypertension induced by pregnancy, pre-eclamptic toxaemia, preeclampsia, preeclampsia/eclampsia, pregnancy associated hypertension, pregnancy toxemia, proteinuric hypertension of pregnancy, and toxaemia of pregnancy.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:idiopathic_progressive_polyneuropathy rdfs:subClassOf :polyneuropathy .
text: idiopathic progressive polyneuropathy is a type of polyneuropathy.

Charcot Marie Tooth disease is a type of neuromuscular disease and has an exact synonym CMT - Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease. It is defined as a neuromuscular disease characterized by a slowly progressive degeneration of the muscles of the foot, lower leg, hand, and forearm.

Pleural tuberculosis is a type of extrapulmonary tuberculosis, allergic disease, pleural disease, and it represents a condition that necessarily involves symptoms such as pleural effusion and allergic reactions. This disease specifically occurs in the pleura. It is defined as an extrapulmonary tuberculosis that leads to a lymphocyte-predominant exudative pleural effusion, situated in the pleura. This condition arises from an allergic reaction to tuberculoprotein, which causes the permeability of the pleural vasculature to change, resulting in a sub-pleural caseous focus rupturing into the pleural sac. Pleural tuberculosis is also known by several exact synonyms, including Pearly disease, Tuberculosis of pleura, Tuberculous pleurisy, Tuberculous pleuritis, and Tuberculous pleurisy in primary progressive tuberculosis.

Hartnup disease is a type of amino acid metabolic disorder and is also characterized as something that involves at least the phenotype of aminoaciduria. It is defined as an amino acid metabolic disorder caused by abnormalities of the renal tubules, which is notably characterized by aminoaciduria involving only monocarboxylic monoamines, a dry red scaly rash, and episodic muscular incoordination due to the effects of the disease on the cerebellum. Hartnup disease is exactly synonymous with the neutral amino acid transport defect and is also referred to as a deficiency of tryptophan oxygenase. Additionally, it is known by another exact synonym, the neutral 1 amino acid transport defect.

Chronic tic disorder is a type of tic disorder and is also known as chronic motor or vocal tic disorder. It is defined as a tic disorder characterized by single or multiple motor or phonic tics, but not both, which are present for more than a year. Additionally, chronic tic disorder is a condition that, at a minimum, manifests some phonic tics.
Glucose intolerance is a type of hyperglycemia and has exact synonyms, including Glucose malabsorption and Malabsorption of glucose.

Lactose intolerance is a type of carbohydrate metabolic disorder characterized by the impaired ability to digest lactose. It is also known as LM - Lactose malabsorption, which is an exact synonym. Moreover, it has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) with the identifier D007787.

Short bowel syndrome is a type of intestinal disease characterized by a reduced ability to absorb nutrients due to the physical loss or the loss of function of a portion of the small and/or large intestine. It is also known by its exact synonyms, acquired short bowel syndrome and short gut syndrome.

Blind loop syndrome is a type of intestinal disease that is characterized by a dysbalance of the bacterial flora of the small intestine, causing derangement to the normal physiological processes of digestion and absorption. It also has an exact synonym, Bacterial overgrowth syndrome.

Tropical sprue is a type of intestinal disease and it is also known by its exact synonyms, Sprue - tropical and Tropical steatorrhea. Additionally, it is characterized by at least one symptom, which includes steatorrhea.

Celiac disease, also known precisely as celiac sprue, coeliac disease, and idiopathic steatorrhea, is a type of autoimmune disease of the gastrointestinal tract. It is characterized by a reaction occurring in the small intestine to gliadin, a prolamin (gluten protein) found in wheat, and similar proteins found in crops of the tribe Triticeae. This condition is closely associated with the HLA-DQ gene. The symptoms of celiac disease include abdominal pain, nausea, diarrhea, vomiting, and constipation. Furthermore, the disease's definition highlights that it causes symptoms such as abdominal pain, constipation, diarrhea, nausea and vomiting, and loss of appetite.

Rickets is a type of bone remodeling disease, defined as a bone remodeling disease that has its material basis in impaired mineralization or calcification of bones before epiphyseal closure due to deficiency or impaired metabolism of vitamin D, phosphorus, or calcium, which results in softening and deformity located in bone. It has the exact synonym "active rickets" and an exact match with the MESH identifier D012279.

Pancreatic steatorrhea is a type of pancreas disease and is also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some steatorrhea. Additionally, pancreatic steatorrhea has an exact synonym: pancreatic steatorrhoea.
Protein losing enteropathy is a type of intestinal disease, which is also precisely known as Enteropathy, exudative, or Exudative enteropathy.

Allergic urticaria is a type of allergic disease, urticaria, and something that at least has symptom some allergic reaction. It is defined as an urticaria characterized by erythematous papules and plaques, with symptoms including pruritis, and has a material basis in an allergic reaction.

Acute gonococcal cervicitis is a type of acute cervicitis, which is defined as an acute cervicitis caused by gonorrhea. It has exact synonyms, including Gonococcal cervicitis and acute gonorrhea of the cervix.
Acute cervicitis is a type of cervicitis that is defined as a cervicitis characterized by onset within the past 1 - 3 days.

Lymph node cancer, also known as lymph node neoplasm, is identified as a cancer that intersects with a disease located in the lymph node. It is categorized as a type of lymphatic system cancer and also as a type of lymph node disease. The definition of lymph node cancer is a lymphatic system cancer that is located in the lymph node.

Fanconi syndrome is a type of renal tubular transport disease, defined as a renal tubular transport disease of the proximal renal tubes characterized by glucosuria, phosphaturia, generalized aminoaciduria, and HCO3 wasting. It has exact synonyms including Congenital Fanconi syndrome, De Toni-Fanconi syndrome, Fanconi-de Toni syndrome, Fanconi-de-Toni syndrome, Infantile nephropathic cystinosis, Lignac-Fanconi syndrome, adult Fanconi Anemia, adult Fanconi syndrome, and deToni Fanconi syndrome. Moreover, Fanconi syndrome has an exact match with the MESH identifier D005198.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:primary_optic_atrophy rdfs:subClassOf :optic_atrophy .
text: primary optic atrophy is a type of optic atrophy.
Microphthalmia is a type of eye disease characterized by one or both eyeballs being abnormally small. It is also exactly synonymous with microphthalmos and simple microphthalmos.
Interstitial nephritis, which is a type of nephritis, has the exact synonym of renal tubulo-interstitial disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:partial_optic_atrophy rdfs:subClassOf :optic_atrophy .
text: partial optic atrophy is a type of optic atrophy.
Wolfram syndrome is a type of syndrome defined as a syndrome that is characterized by diabetes mellitus, optic atrophy, and deafness. It has exact synonyms WFS and WS.

Cystinosis is a type of autosomal recessive disease and a lysosomal storage disease that is characterized by the abnormal accumulation of cystine in the lysosomes. It follows an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern and has its material basis in mutations in the CTNS gene, located on chromosome 17. Additionally, cystinosis is exactly synonymous with cystine storage disease.

Schizotypal personality disorder, which is a type of personality disorder, is defined as a condition that involves a need for social isolation, anxiety in social situations, odd behavior and thinking, and often unconventional beliefs.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:acute_inferoposterior_infarction rdfs:subClassOf :acute_myocardial_infarction .
text: acute inferoposterior infarction is a type of acute myocardial infarction.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:acute_inferolateral_myocardial_infarction rdfs:subClassOf :acute_myocardial_infarction .
text: acute inferolateral myocardial infarction is a type of acute myocardial infarction.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:acute_anterolateral_myocardial_infarction rdfs:subClassOf :acute_myocardial_infarction .
text: acute anterolateral myocardial infarction is a type of acute myocardial infarction.

Alzheimer's disease is a type of tauopathy with a definition that encompasses it being a tauopathy characterized by memory lapses, confusion, emotional instability, and progressive loss of mental ability. It results in progressive memory loss, impaired thinking, disorientation, and changes in personality and mood, which, in advanced cases, lead to a profound decline in cognitive and physical functioning. It is marked histologically by the degeneration of brain neurons, especially in the cerebral cortex, and by the presence of neurofibrillary tangles and plaques containing beta-amyloid. Additionally, Alzheimer's disease has the exact synonyms "Alzheimer disease" and "Alzheimer's dementia".

Lipoma of the colon is a type of colonic disease, and it is also classified as a type of large intestine lipoma. Furthermore, it is a type of condition that specifically occurs in the colon. Additionally, Lipoma of the colon is exactly synonymous with Colonic Lipoma.
Colon leiomyoma is a type of colonic disease that at least derives from some smooth muscle cell and has its location in the colon. It is also exactly synonymous with Colonic leiomyoma.
Colonic lymphangioma is a type of colonic benign neoplasm, which is also exactly known as Lymphangioma of the colon.
The residual stage of open angle glaucoma is a type of open angle glaucoma, which also goes by the exact synonym "Open-angle glaucoma residual stage."

Mediastinum neuroblastoma, which is a type of malignant mediastinal neurogenic neoplasm, is defined as a malignant mediastinal neurogenic neoplasm that has its material basis in immature nerve cells. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with neuroblastoma of mediastinum.
Mediastinum ganglioneuroblastoma is a type of malignant mediastinal neurogenic neoplasm, which is exactly synonymous with Ganglioneuroblastoma of the mediastinum.

Open angle glaucoma is a type of glaucoma characterized by optic nerve damage resulting in progressive loss of visual field and increased pressure in the eye due to trabecular blockage. It is also known by several exact synonyms including wide-angle glaucoma, glaucoma simplex, open angle glaucoma itself, and pigmentary glaucoma.

Juvenile glaucoma is an autosomal dominant disease and a subtype of primary open-angle glaucoma. It is characterized by having a material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance and typically begins during young adult onset. Juvenile glaucoma is defined as a primary open-angle glaucoma that has an early age of onset, is rapidly progressive with more severely elevated and fluctuating intraocular pressures. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with Glaucoma of childhood.

Separation anxiety disorder is a type of anxiety disorder that is defined by an excessive and inappropriate level of anxiety over being separated from a person to whom the individual has a strong emotional attachment or a place.

Lactocele, which is a type of breast cyst, is defined as a breast cyst that develops during or shortly after lactation. It is characterized by the retention of milk or a milky substance, usually located in the mammary glands. Furthermore, lactocele is exactly synonymous with Galactocele.

Hypertrophy of the breast is a type of breast disease that is characterized by the progressive, excessive enlargement of breast connective tissue. It has exact synonyms including "breasts enlarged" and "large breast."

Mastitis is a type of breast disease, which is characterized by a painful infection of the breast tissue. It has exact synonyms including Inflammatory breast disease, Inflammatory disease of breast, and breast inflammation.
Fat necrosis of the breast is a type of breast disease characterized by the death of breast adipocytes, usually secondary to injury. It is also exactly synonymous with breast fat necrosis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chronic_endophthalmitis rdfs:subClassOf :purulent_endophthalmitis .
text: chronic endophthalmitis is a type of purulent endophthalmitis.

Paragonimiasis is a type of disease that is classified under several categories including splenic disease, liver disease, parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease, and brain disease. This indicates that it can affect various organs such as the brain, spleen, and liver. The disease has a material basis in parasites of the genus Paragonimus. Symptoms of paragonimiasis include hepatosplenomegaly, urticaria, abdominal pain, hemoptysis, diarrhea, fever, and cough. A detailed definition of paragonimiasis describes it as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease involving infection by flukes of the genus Paragonimus. In its acute phase, symptoms can range from diarrhea, abdominal pain, fever, and cough to urticaria, hepatosplenomegaly, pulmonary abnormalities, and eosinophilia. Pulmonary manifestations may include coughing, expectoration of discolored sputum, hemoptysis, and chest radiographic abnormalities, with potential infection in various organs like the brain, spleen, and liver. Additionally, paragonimiasis is known by several exact synonyms, including infection by Paragonimus, lung fluke disease, lung fluke infection, and pulmonary paragonimiasis.

Primary open angle glaucoma is a type of open angle glaucoma that is characterized by the absence of any apparent obstruction of aqueous outflow through the trabecular meshwork with gonioscopy, but often with elevated intraocular pressure. It is also exactly synonymous with chronic simple glaucoma.

Giardiasis is a type of parasitic protozoa infectious disease which has a material basis in the Giardia intestinalis. It is characterized by several symptoms, including steatorrhea, bloating, abdominal pain, nausea, diarrhea, and vomiting. Giardiasis involves the infection of the small intestine by the single-celled enteric protozoan parasite Giardia intestinalis, leading to symptoms such as greasy and malodorous stools, diarrhea, abdominal pain, bloating, nausea, and vomiting. Additionally, giardiasis is precisely known as an infection by Giardia lamblia and is also referred to as beaver fever.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:toxic_diffuse_goiter rdfs:subClassOf :hyperthyroidism .
text: toxic diffuse goiter is a type of hyperthyroidism.

Renal hypertension is the same as something that is at the intersection of hypertension and a disease that has its location in the kidney. It is a type of secondary hypertension as well as a type of kidney disease.

Kidney failure is a type of kidney disease and is defined as a kidney disease characterized by the failure of the kidneys to adequately filter waste products from the blood. Additionally, kidney failure has an exact synonym, which is renal failure.
Cerebral lipidosis is a type of cerebral degeneration and also a type of condition that is characterized by the presence of disease in the cerebrum.

The broad ligament malignant neoplasm is identical to a condition that is both a cancer and a disease located in the broad ligament of the uterus. It is categorized as a type of uterine adnexa cancer. This specific neoplasm is defined as a uterine adnexa cancer situated in the broad ligament. Additionally, it is precisely synonymous with the malignant neoplasm of the broad ligament of the uterus.
Otitis media is a type of middle ear disease and is defined as an otitis that involves inflammation of the middle ear.

Petrositis is a type of osteomyelitis, which is an osteomyelitis that has its material basis in an infection located in the petrous part of the temporal bone. It is exactly synonymous with both acute petrositis and chronic petrositis. Additionally, petrositis is relatedly synonymous with the inflammation of the petrous bone.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chronic_pyelonephritis rdfs:subClassOf :pyelonephritis .
text: chronic pyelonephritis is a type of pyelonephritis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:portal_hypertension rdfs:subClassOf :hepatic_vascular_disease .
text: portal hypertension is a type of hepatic vascular disease.

Hypertension is a type of artery disease and is also a condition that always includes the symptom of high blood pressure. It is defined as an artery disease characterized by chronic elevated blood pressure in the arteries. Hypertension is exactly synonymous with HTN, hyperpiesia, and vascular hypertensive disorder. Additionally, it has a related synonym, hypertensive disease.
Thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura is a type of thrombophilia and has an exact synonym, Moschcowitz's syndrome.

Bubonic plague is a type of plague, lymph node disease, and is transmitted at least in part by flea-borne transmission. It is characterized by symptoms such as prostration, fever, lymphadenitis, and chills, and the disease specifically affects the lymph nodes. The bubonic plague, also known as the Black Death, is defined as a plague that results in an infection located in the lymph node, producing a bubo. This condition involves inflamed, necrotic, and hemorrhagic lymphoid tissue, with symptoms including enlarged and tender lymph nodes, fever, chills, and prostration.

Fiedler's myocarditis is a type of acute myocarditis and is also a type of condition that at least has some symptoms of myocarditis. Furthermore, Fiedler's myocarditis is exactly synonymous with Idiopathic myocarditis, Isolated (Fiedler's) myocarditis, and Fiedler myocarditis.

Septic myocarditis is a type of acute myocarditis and is also classified under conditions that at least manifest some symptoms of myocarditis. It is defined as an acute myocarditis characterized by an underlying infectious insult to the myocardium that induces acute inflammation.

Primary polycythemia is a type of polycythemia defined as a polycythemia that has a material basis in factors intrinsic to red cell precursors. It is also exactly synonymous with Familiar Polycythemia and familial erythrocytosis.
Mesenteric lymphadenitis is a type of lymphadenitis and has an exact synonym, Mesenteric adenitis.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:methemoglobinemia rdfs:subClassOf :hemoglobinopathy .
text: methemoglobinemia is a type of hemoglobinopathy.

Queensland tick typhus, also known precisely as Australian tick typhus and Rickettsia australis spotted fever, with a related synonym being North Queensland tick typhus, is a type of spotted fever. It has a material basis in Rickettsia australis and is transmitted by ticks, specifically Ixodes holocyclus, as well as through tick borne transmission. The infection manifests with symptoms such as fever, headache, enlargement of lymph nodes, maculopapular rash, and lymphadenopathy.
Premature menopause is a type of ovarian dysfunction, which is defined as the loss of normal ovarian function before age 40. It has the exact synonyms "Menopause - premature" and "Menopause praecox."

Setariasis is a type of filariasis that involves a parasitic infection of the abdomen in cattle, horses, and sheep by nematodes of the genus Setaria. It is also exactly synonymous with "Infectious Disease by Setaria."

Chronic frontal sinusitis, a specific type of frontal sinusitis, is defined as a condition where the inflammation lasts for 12 weeks or more. This leads to symptoms such as a steady headache, localized tenderness, and intermittent, purulent nasal and postnasal drainage.

Frontal sinusitis is a type of sinusitis, defined as a condition involving the infection of the frontal sinuses located over the eyes in the brow area. This condition causes pain or pressure in the frontal sinus cavity and headache over the forehead.
Chronic maxillary sinusitis is a type of maxillary sinusitis, defined as a maxillary sinusitis which lasts for 12 weeks or more. It is also exactly synonymous with chronic antritis.

Chronic sphenoidal sinusitis is a type of sphenoid sinusitis characterized by its definition as a sphenoid sinusitis which lasts for 12 weeks or more. It is also exactly synonymous with Sphenoidal sinus-chr.

Sphenoid sinusitis is a type of sinusitis, which is specifically an infection of the sphenoid sinuses. This condition causes pain or pressure behind the eyes, but it is often associated with pain at the vertex of the head as well. Additionally, sphenoid sinusitis is exactly synonymous with Sphenoidal sinusitis.

Filariasis is a type of parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease and also a type of condition that at least has a material basis in some Filarioidea. It is defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the lymphatics and subcutaneous tissue by nematodes of the superfamily Filarioidea. Additionally, filariasis has the exact synonym "disease due to superfamily Filarioidea" and has an exact match with MESH:D005368.
Acute gonococcal epididymo orchitis is a type of epididymo orchitis and is exactly synonymous with Gonococcal epididymo-orchitis.
