@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:gastric_ulcer rdfs:subClassOf :peptic_ulcer_disease ;
    :has_exact_synonym "acute gastric ulcer with haemorrhage and perforation"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage AND with perforation but without obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage and obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage and perforation"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage and perforation, with obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage and perforation, without mention of obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage, with obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage, with perforation AND with obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with perforation"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with perforation AND obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer with perforation, with obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer without hemorrhage and without perforation"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer without hemorrhage, without perforation AND without obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastric ulcer without mention of hemorrhage or perforation, without mention of obstruction"@en,
        "bleeding acute gastric ulcer"@en,
        "chronic gastric ulcer without hemorrhage AND without perforation"@en,
        "chronic gastric ulcer without hemorrhage AND without perforation but with obstruction"@en,
        "chronic gastric ulcer without mention of hemorrhage or perforation, with obstruction"@en .
text:
Gastric ulcer is a type of peptic ulcer disease and has various exact synonyms based on its characteristics. It is synonymous with acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage and perforation, and this term also encompasses acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage and perforation but without obstruction. Additionally, it includes acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage and obstruction, acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage and perforation with obstruction, and acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage and perforation without mention of obstruction. Gastric ulcer is also identified as acute gastric ulcer with hemorrhage, with obstruction, and with perforation and obstruction. The term further extends to acute gastric ulcer with perforation, with both perforation and obstruction, and with perforation with obstruction. It also covers acute gastric ulcer without hemorrhage and without perforation, acute gastric ulcer without hemorrhage, without perforation and without obstruction, and acute gastric ulcer without mention of hemorrhage or perforation and without mention of obstruction. Additionally, it is known as bleeding acute gastric ulcer.

Furthermore, gastric ulcer is referred to as chronic gastric ulcer without hemorrhage and without perforation, including when there is obstruction and when there is no mention of hemorrhage or perforation but with obstruction.

Mansonelliasis is both a type of filariasis and a skin disease, characterized as an affliction that has a presence in certain skin zones. It is defined as a filariasis that involves a parasitic infection by the nematodes Mansonella ozzardi or Mansonella perstans, which reside in the skin or body cavities. This nematode is transmitted through the bite of midges and blackflies.

Tibialis tendinitis is identified as a type of tendinitis and is the same as an intersection of conditions that are categorized as tendinitis and diseases that specifically have their location in the tibialis.

Nasal cavity cancer is defined as a respiratory system cancer that is located in the nasal cavity, and it is the same as something that is an intersection of something that is cancer and something that is at least a disease with a location in the nasal cavity. This type of cancer is also a type of nasal cavity disease. Additionally, nasal cavity cancer has the exact synonyms "malignant neoplasm of nasal cavities" and "malignant tumor of the nasal cavity."

Nasal cavity olfactory neuroblastoma is the same as something that intersects olfactory neuroblastoma and something that, at least, has a disease located in the nasal cavity. It is a type of nasal cavity cancer and also a type of olfactory neuroblastoma. Additionally, nasal cavity olfactory neuroblastoma has the exact synonym "Olfactory neuroblastoma of the nasal cavity."

Nasal cavity lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and a type of nasal cavity cancer. It is a type of condition that at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte. Additionally, nasal cavity lymphoma has exact synonyms, including "Lymphoma of the nasal cavity" and "lymphoma of nasal cavity."

Duodenum adenocarcinoma is a type of duodenum cancer and also a type of adenocarcinoma. It falls under the category of cancers that derive from epithelial cells of glandular origin. Specifically, it is a duodenum cancer that originates from epithelial cells of glandular origin. Additionally, duodenum adenocarcinoma is exactly synonymous with duodenal adenocarcinoma.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:sexual_sadism rdfs:subClassOf :sexual_health_disorder .
text: sexual sadism is a type of sexual health disorder.

Dirofilariasis is a type of filariasis, which is also classified as a skin and lung disease. It specifically falls under the category of diseases that affect both the skin and lung zones. Dirofilariasis, also known exactly as Dirofilaria infectious disease or Infection by Dirofilaria, is defined as a zoonotic infection caused by the nematodes Dirofilaria immitis or Dirofilaria repens. These nematodes are transmitted to humans from animals such as dogs, cats, wolves, and coyotes through infected mosquitoes. The disease typically presents as subcutaneous nodules or pulmonary lesions.
Malignant essential hypertension is a type of essential hypertension and it is exactly synonymous with accelerated essential hypertension.

Malignant hypertension is a type of hypertension that is characterized by a rapid onset of extremely high blood pressure. It is also identified as a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some high blood pressure.

Essential hypertension is a type of hypertension that is defined as hypertension with no known cause and is the most common type of hypertension. Additionally, it has exact synonyms "idiopathic hypertension" and "primary hypertension."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:voyeurism rdfs:subClassOf :paraphilia_disorder .
text: voyeurism is a type of paraphilia disorder.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chylocele_of_tunica_vaginalis rdfs:subClassOf :male_reproductive_system_disease .
text: chylocele of tunica vaginalis is a type of male reproductive system disease.

Eastern Equine Encephalitis (EEE) is a viral infectious disease that also falls under the category of a brain disease. It manifests with various symptoms including disorientation, seizures, headaches, coma, high fever, vomiting, and chills. This disease specifically targets the brain. EEE is defined as a viral infectious disease leading to inflammation in the brain of horses and humans, caused by the Eastern Equine Encephalitis virus. This virus is transmitted through the bite of infected Aedes, Coquillettidia, and Culex species of mosquitoes. The infection is characterized by a sudden onset of symptoms such as headache, high fever, chills, vomiting, disorientation, seizures, and coma. Additionally, Eastern Equine Encephalitis is also known by its exact synonym, Neuroinvasive Eastern Equine Encephalitis Virus Infection, and has a related synonym, EEE.

Murray Valley encephalitis is a type of viral infectious disease and brain disease that has a material basis in the Murray Valley encephalitis virus and is transmitted by Culex annulirostris mosquitoes. This disease is characterized by several symptoms including confusion, drowsiness, weakness, nausea, headache, fever, and vomiting. Moreover, it specifically affects the brain. The detailed definition of Murray Valley encephalitis outlines it as a viral infectious disease resulting in inflammation located in the brain, caused by the Murray Valley encephalitis virus, transmitted by Culex annulirostris mosquitoes. The infection manifests with symptoms such as fever, headache, nausea, vomiting, drowsiness, confusion, fitting, and weakness. Additionally, Murray Valley encephalitis is also known by its exact synonyms: Australian X disease and Australian encephalitis.

Western equine encephalitis (WEE) is a viral infectious disease that also categorizes as a brain disease. Its material basis is found in the Western equine encephalitis virus, and it is transmitted by species within the Culex genus. This disease manifests through various symptoms, including weakness, nausea, headache, anorexia, fever, altered mental status, vomiting, and malaise. Additionally, the disease primarily affects the brain in both horses and humans. It is characterized by inflammation in the brain caused by the Western equine encephalomyelitis virus, which is transmitted by both Culex and Aedes species of mosquitoes. The infection is identified by symptoms such as fever, headache, nausea, vomiting, anorexia, malaise, altered mental status, and weakness.

Japanese Encephalitis, also known as Japanese B Encephalitis, is a type of viral infectious disease and brain disease that has a material basis in the Japanese Encephalitis virus. It is transmitted by the Culex tritaeniorhynchus mosquito. This disease is characterized by several symptoms, including confusion, disorientation, tremor, stiff neck, stupor, headache, convulsion, coma, spastic paralysis, and high fever. Moreover, Japanese Encephalitis is specifically located in the brain. The detailed definition of Japanese Encephalitis outlines it as a viral infectious disease that results in an infection located in the brain, caused by the Japanese Encephalitis virus, and transmitted by the bite of a Culex tritaeniorhynchus mosquito. The infection manifests with symptoms such as headache, high fever, neck stiffness, stupor, disorientation, coma, tremors, convulsions, and spastic paralysis.

St. Louis encephalitis is a type of viral infectious disease that results in inflammation located in the brain. It has a material basis in the St. Louis encephalitis virus and is transmitted by mosquitoes of the Culex genus. This disease is characterized by a variety of symptoms, including confusion, disorientation, tremor, stiff neck, stupor, headache, convulsion, coma, spastic paralysis, and high fever. Furthermore, St. Louis encephalitis has the exact synonym "Neuroinvasive St. Louis encephalitis virus infection."

Angiodysplasia of the intestine is the same as the intersection of angiodysplasia and a disease that is located in the intestine. It is a type of angiodysplasia, and also a type of intestinal disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:sexual_masochism rdfs:subClassOf :sexual_health_disorder .
text: sexual masochism is a type of sexual health disorder.

Edwards syndrome is a type of chromosomal duplication syndrome, which is characterized by slow growth before birth, a low birth weight, and has its material basis in three copies of chromosome 18. This condition is also exactly known as Complete trisomy 18 syndrome, E3 Trisomy, and trisomy 18.

Middle ear cholesterol granuloma is a type of otitis media and is also a specific kind of something that at least exhibits the phenotype of some granuloma. It is defined as an otitis media that manifests as an expansile, inflammatory mass of granulation tissue in the middle ear, which is essentially a foreign body reaction to cholesterol deposits occurring in obstructed fluid-filled air cells of the temporal bone. This condition presents with a conductive hearing loss and a blue eardrum. Additionally, middle ear cholesterol granuloma is exactly synonymous with Cholesterin granuloma and Cholesterin granuloma of the middle ear.

Salivary gland disease is identified as an intersection of diseases that are located in the saliva-secreting gland, indicating it is the same as a condition that is both a disease and has its location in some saliva secreting gland. It is also characterized as a type of mouth disease. This disease is defined as a mouth disease that is located in the salivary gland. Furthermore, salivary gland disease is exactly synonymous with Non-neoplastic Salivary gland disease.
Paralytic squint is a type of strabismus, and it has exact synonyms including Incomitant dissociation and Paralytic strabismus.

Partial third nerve palsy is a type of paralytic squint. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Partial third nerve palsy, Third nerve palsy with pupil sparing, and Third or oculomotor nerve palsy, partial.

Abducens nerve palsy, which is the same as something that intersects with a disease and something that at least has a location in the abducens nerve, is a type of cranial nerve palsy. It is defined as a cranial nerve palsy characterized by lateral rectus muscle weakness resulting from damage to the abducens (sixth cranial) nerve. It has several exact synonyms including Abducens nerve weakness, Lateral rectus muscle denervation paresis, Lateral rectus muscle innervation disorder, Sixth cranial nerve disorder, Sixth nerve palsy, VIth nerve Paralysis, VIth nerve disorder, abducens nerve disease, and abducens palsy.
Total third nerve palsy is a type of paralytic squint. It is also precisely known as Third nerve palsy with pupil involved, Third or oculomotor nerve palsy, total, and Total third nerve palsy.
Fourth cranial nerve palsy, which is a type of paralytic squint, has exact synonyms including Fourth nerve palsy and Fourth or trochlear nerve palsy.

Age-related macular degeneration (AMD) is a type of degeneration of the macula and posterior pole, which is an autosomal dominant disease. It is characterized by a degeneration that has its material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. AMD is defined as a degeneration of the macula and posterior pole that leads to a loss of vision in the center of the visual field due to retina damage, which results in the blurring of sharp central vision. Furthermore, age-related macular degeneration is also known by exact synonyms such as Age-Related Maculopathies, Age-Related Maculopathy, Senile macular degeneration, Senile macular retinal degeneration, and age-related macular degeneration.

Kuhnt Junius degeneration is a type of degeneration of the macula and posterior pole. It is exactly synonymous with Exudative senile macular degeneration of the retina, Neovascular age-related macular degeneration, Senile macular degeneration, wet, and Wet senile macular retinal degeneration.

Meningocele is a type of spina bifida and is defined as a spina bifida characterized by the herniation of the meninges between the vertebrae. Furthermore, it has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) with the identifier D008588.

Iliac vein thrombophlebitis is defined as a condition that represents the intersection of thrombophlebitis and any disease that occurs in the iliac vein. It is a specific type of thrombophlebitis. Additionally, iliac vein thrombophlebitis is exactly synonymous with Phlebitis and thrombophlebitis of the iliac vein.

Hand, foot, and mouth disease is a viral infectious disease primarily caused by the coxsackievirus A16 and enterovirus A71. It is transmitted through contact transmission and vehicle-borne fomite transmission. This disease manifests symptoms such as rash, fever, malaise, and pharynx inflammation. It specifically affects the mouth, foot, and hand, indicating the areas of the body where the disease has its location. Additionally, hand, foot, and mouth disease is characterized by infection located in the skin and is transmitted by contaminated fomites, as well as contact with nose and throat secretions, saliva, blister fluid, and stool of infected persons. The infection leads to symptoms including fever, poor appetite, malaise, sore throat, painful sores in the mouth, and a skin rash on the palms of the hands and soles of the feet. The disease is also known by the exact synonym "Vesicular stomatitis and exanthem."

Epidemic pleurodynia is a type of muscular disease as well as a viral infectious disease, and it has a material basis in some enterovirus b. This disease is characterized by several symptoms, including necrosis, headache, fever, severe chest pain, and malaise. Furthermore, it is a condition that primarily affects muscle tissue. Epidemic pleurodynia is defined as a viral infectious disease resulting in necrosis located in the intercostal muscle, caused by Human enterovirus B. The infection manifests with symptoms such as severe chest pain, fever, malaise, pleuritis, and headache. Additionally, epidemic pleurodynia is known by various exact synonyms including Bamble disease, Bornholm disease, Epidemic pleurisy, Epidemic myositis, devil's grip, and epidemic myalgia.

Herpangina is defined as a viral infectious disease that results in infection located in the mouth. It is characterized as a type of mouth disease and a type of viral infectious disease. The disease has a material basis in viruses, specifically in a group that includes Human coxsackievirus A16, Human enterovirus 71, group B coxsackievirus, or echoviruses. These viruses are transmitted through various means, including contact transmission, droplet spread transmission, and vehicle borne ingestion transmission. The infection manifests with symptoms such as fever, lesions in the mouth, and pharynx inflammation. Additionally, herpangina is recognized by the exact synonym Vesicular pharyngitis.

Lepromatous leprosy is a type of leprosy that is transmitted at least in part by droplet spread. It is defined as a leprosy resulting in early cutaneous lesions which consist of pale macules that are small, diffuse, and symmetric. This form is characterized by hypoesthesia over the extensor surfaces of the distal extremities, alopecia affecting the lateral aspects of the eyebrows, saddle-nose deformity, and oral lepromas. Additionally, lepromatous leprosy is exactly synonymous with type L leprosy.
Tethered spinal cord syndrome is a type of spinal cord disease and has an exact synonym, spinal dysraphism. Additionally, it has an exact match with NCI:C99080.

Hypospadias is a type of physical disorder, which is characterized by an abnormally placed urethral opening on the underside of the penis or on the perineum. It is also exactly synonymous with familial hypospadias.

Microcephaly is a type of congenital nervous system abnormality characterized by a significantly smaller than normal head in infants. It is defined as a congenital nervous system abnormality and has exact synonyms like Microcephalus and microencephaly. Additionally, microcephaly has an exact match with MESH:D008831.

Hydrocephalus is a type of cerebral degeneration and is also known as a condition that affects the cerebrum, a specific location related to diseases. It is defined as a cerebral degeneration characterized by an abnormal accumulation of cerebrospinal fluid in the ventricles of the brain, leading to progressive enlargement of the head. Furthermore, hydrocephalus is exactly synonymous with both hydrocephalus, X-linked, and hydrocephalus, nonsyndromic, autosomal recessive.

Tooth disease, which is also exactly synonymous with teeth disease, is defined as a mouth disease that is located in the teeth. It is identified as a type of mouth disease. Furthermore, tooth disease is equivalent to an intersection comprising something that is a disease and something that has at least a disease located in some calcareous tooth.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:benign_essential_hypertension rdfs:subClassOf :essential_hypertension .
text: benign essential hypertension is a type of essential hypertension.

Amnestic disorder is a type of cognitive disorder characterized by a disturbance or loss of memory. It involves the loss of previously established memories, the loss of the ability to create new memories, or the loss of the ability to learn new information. Amnestic disorder is also exactly synonymous with Amnestic syndrome, Korsakoff's psychosis or syndrome, and amnesia.

Wernicke Korsakoff syndrome is a type of thiamine deficiency disease characterized by a nutritional deficiency that manifests as ophthalmoplegia, ataxia, a change in mental status, and an acute onset of severe memory impairment without any dysfunction in intellectual abilities, all due to a lack of thiamine. Furthermore, Wernicke Korsakoff syndrome is also known by several exact synonyms, including Korsakoff Syndrome, Korsakoff's psychosis, Korsakoff's syndrome, Korsakov psychosis, and Korsakov's psychosis.

Siberian tick typhus is a type of spotted fever and is also exactly known as North Asian tick fever, North Asian tick typhus, Rickettsia sibirica spotted fever, and Manchurian typhus. It has a material basis in Rickettsia sibirica and is transmitted by ticks, specifically Dermacentor marginatus, Haemaphysalis concinna, and through tick-borne transmission. The symptoms of Siberian tick typhus include fever, maculopapular rash, and eschar. Additionally, the definition of Siberian tick typhus highlights that it is a spotted fever caused by Rickettsia sibirica, transmitted by Dermacentor nuttalli, Dermacentor marginatus, and Haemaphysalis concinna ticks, and presents symptoms such as fever, eschar, regional adenopathy, and maculopapular rash.

Sickle cell anemia is classified as a type of autosomal recessive disease, blood protein disease, and something that fundamentally has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined as a blood protein disease characterized by a low number of red blood cells, repeated infections, and periodic episodes of pain. These symptoms result from abnormal hemoglobin molecules called hemoglobin S, which can distort red blood cells into a sickle or crescent shape. Sickle cell anemia is also known by several exact synonyms, including Hb SC disease, Hb-S/Hb-C disease, Hb-SS disease without crisis, Hemoglobin S disease without crisis, Sickle-cell/Hb-C disease without crisis, drepanocytosis, haemoglobin SC disease, hemoglobin SC disease, and sickle cell anaemia.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:gastrojejunal_ulcer rdfs:subClassOf :peptic_ulcer_disease ;
    :has_exact_synonym "acute gastrojejunal ulcer with hemorrhage"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer with hemorrhage AND obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer with hemorrhage AND perforation"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer with hemorrhage and perforation, with obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer with hemorrhage, with perforation AND with obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer with perforation"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer with perforation AND obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer with perforation, with obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer without hemorrhage AND without perforation"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer without hemorrhage, without perforation AND without obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer without mention of hemorrhage or perforation, without mention of obstruction"@en,
        "acute gastrojejunal ulcer, with hemorrhage, with obstruction"@en,
        "chronic gastrojejunal ulcer without hemorrhage AND without perforation"@en,
        "chronic gastrojejunal ulcer without hemorrhage, without perforation AND without obstruction"@en,
        "chronic gastrojejunal ulcer without mention of hemorrhage or perforation, without mention of obstruction"@en .
text:
Gastrojejunal ulcer, a type of peptic ulcer disease, is associated with a diverse range of exact synonyms that describe its various states and complications. These synonyms include acute gastrojejunal ulcer with hemorrhage, which can further be specified with additional complications such as obstruction and perforation, leading to descriptions like acute gastrojejunal ulcer with hemorrhage and obstruction, acute gastrojejunal ulcer with hemorrhage and perforation, and acute gastrojejunal ulcer with hemorrhage, perforation, and obstruction. Similarly, acute gastrojejunal ulcer with perforation is another variation, which can also include obstruction as a complication, expressed as acute gastrojejunal ulcer with perforation and obstruction.

Additionally, there are descriptions for acute gastrojejunal ulcers without certain complications, such as acute gastrojejunal ulcer without hemorrhage and without perforation, with further specificity available indicating the absence of obstruction as well. This specificity extends to acute gastrojejunal ulcer without mention of hemorrhage or perforation, and without mention of obstruction, offering a clear delineation of the condition's various manifestations.

The chronic state of gastrojejunal ulcer also has its exact synonyms, characterized by the absence of hemorrhage and perforation, which can similarly be detailed further to indicate the absence of obstruction. These synonyms include chronic gastrojejunal ulcer without hemorrhage and without perforation, chronic gastrojejunal ulcer without hemorrhage, without perforation, and without obstruction, and chronic gastrojejunal ulcer without mention of hemorrhage or perforation, and without mention of obstruction, providing a comprehensive classification system for the disease based on its stage and complications.

Borderline Personality Disorder is a type of personality disorder that is defined as a personality disorder involving a prolonged disturbance of personality function characterized by depth and variability of moods.
Dependent personality disorder is a type of personality disorder characterized by a pervasive psychological dependence on other people.

Obsessive Compulsive Personality Disorder (OCPD) is a type of personality disorder characterized by a pervasive pattern of preoccupation with orderliness, perfectionism, and mental and interpersonal control at the expense of flexibility, openness, and efficiency. It is exactly synonymous with OCPD and is also relatedly referred to as Anankastic Personality Disorder.

Obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD) is a type of anxiety disorder characterized by unwanted and repeated thoughts, feelings, ideas, sensations (obsessions), or behaviors that make individuals feel driven to do something (compulsions). It is also known as Anancastic neurosis and has the exact synonym "obsessive-compulsive disorder."

Multiple personality disorder, which is a type of dissociative disorder, has the definition of being a dissociative disorder that involves the simultaneous display of multiple distinct identities or personalities. It also goes by the exact synonym dissociative identity disorder.

Dissociative disorder is a type of mental health disease characterized by the separation (dissociation) of normally well-integrated functions such as memory, identity, perception, or consciousness. It is also exactly synonymous with dissociative disease and dissociative reaction.

Schizoid personality disorder is a type of personality disorder characterized by a lack of interest in social relationships, a tendency towards a solitary lifestyle, secretiveness, emotional coldness, and sometimes sexual apathy. Additionally, it involves a rich, elaborate, and exclusively internal fantasy world.
Impulse control disorder is a type of mental health disease, defined as a failure to resist an impulsive act or behavior that may be harmful to oneself or others.
Paranoid personality disorder is a type of personality disorder characterized by paranoia and a pervasive, long-standing suspiciousness and generalized mistrust of others.

Antisocial personality disorder is a type of personality disorder with a definition that involves a pervasive pattern of disregard for, and violation of, the rights of others that begins in childhood or early adolescence and continues into adulthood. It has exact synonyms such as Asocial personality, Dissocial personality disorder, Psychopath personality, Psychopathic personality, Psychopathic personality disorder, and Sociopathic personality.

Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD) is a type of specific developmental disorder that is characterized by the co-existence of attentional problems and hyperactivity, where each behavior occurs infrequently alone, and symptoms start before seven years of age. This condition is also recognized as a type of disorder that at least has the symptom of some hyperactivity. Furthermore, ADHD is precisely known by several exact synonyms, including Attention Deficit Disorder and Hyperkinetic Disorder.
Intracranial aneurysm, which is a type of cerebral arterial disease, is exactly synonymous with brain aneurysm.

Tongue disease is the same as something that intersects with something that has a disease, and something that at least has a disease located in the tongue. Additionally, tongue disease is a type of mouth disease and is defined as a mouth disease located in the tongue.

Nephritis is a type of kidney disease and also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some inflammation. It is defined as a kidney disease characterized by an inflammation of the kidneys.

Strongyloidiasis is a type of disease that affects various parts of the body including the central nervous system, skin, intestines, and lungs. It is categorized as both a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease and intersects with diseases that have locations in the skin, intestine, central nervous system, and lungs. The material basis of strongyloidiasis is the nematode Strongyloides stercoralis. It is defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection of the intestine, lungs, skin, and central nervous system with the nematode Strongyloides stercoralis. Additionally, strongyloidiasis is exactly synonymous with both "Infection by Strongyloides" and "disseminated strongyloidiasis."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:cholesteatoma_of_attic rdfs:subClassOf :cholesteatoma_of_middle_ear .
text: cholesteatoma of attic is a type of cholesteatoma of middle ear.

Cholesteatoma of the middle ear is the same as the intersection of something that is both a cholesteatoma and a disease with a location in the middle ear. It is a type of middle ear disease as well as a type of cholesteatoma. Cholesteatoma of the middle ear is exactly synonymous with several terms including Cholesteatoma of the middle ear and mastoid, Cholesteatoma of the middle ear and/or mastoid, Cholesteatoma of the middle ear, Epidermosis of the ear, Epidermosis of the middle ear, cholesteatoma, and middle ear cholesteatoma.

Spastic diplegia is a type of spastic cerebral palsy. It is defined as a spastic cerebral palsy that affects lower extremities, resulting in tight leg and hip muscles. This condition causes the legs to cross at the knees, making it difficult to walk. Spastic diplegia is also known by several exact synonyms, including Diplegic infantile cerebral palsy, Infantile spastic cerebral palsy, Little's disease, Littles disease, cerebral spastic infantile paralysis, and infantile diplegic cerebral palsy.

Lipoid nephrosis is a type of nephrotic syndrome and it is also known by several exact synonyms, including Minimal Change Glomerulonephritis, Minimal Change Disease, Nephrotic Syndrome with Lesion of Minimal Change Glomerulonephritis, and Nephrotic Syndrome with Lesion of Minimal Change Nephrotic Syndrome.

Spastic hemiplegia is a type of spastic cerebral palsy characterized by affecting one side of the body, resulting in a stiff arm, hand, and leg. On the affected side, the arm and leg may not develop normally. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Congenital hemiplegia, Hemiplegic infantile cerebral palsy, hemiplegic cerebral palsy, and spastic hemiplegic cerebral palsy.

Spastic monoplegia is a type of spastic cerebral palsy characterized by the affliction of only one limb. It is precisely defined as a spastic cerebral palsy that affects only one limb. This condition is also exactly synonymous with monoplegic infantile cerebral palsy, infantile monoplegic cerebral palsy, and spastic monoplegic cerebral palsy.

Hemiplegia is a type of central nervous system disease, which is defined as a central nervous system disease that is characterized by the complete paralysis of half of the body. It also has the exact synonyms "Infantile hemiplegia" and "Postnatal infantile hemiplegia."

Spastic quadriplegic cerebral palsy is a type of spastic cerebral palsy characterized by non-progressive, variable spastic quadriparesis in multiple family members, in the absence of additional factors complicating pregnancy or birth. It affects all four limbs, with individuals having difficulty walking and talking. This condition is also known by exact synonyms, including inherited congenital spastic quadriplegia, inherited congenital spastic tetraplegia, quadriplegic infantile cerebral palsy, spastic quadriplegia, and tetraplegic infantile cerebral palsy.
Acute salpingo-oophoritis is a type of salpingo-oophoritis and has the exact synonyms acute salpingitis and oophoritis.
Salpingo oophoritis is a type of oophoritis and it has exact synonyms Salpingitis/oophoritis and Tubo-ovarian inflammatory disease.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:acute_salpingitis rdfs:subClassOf :salpingitis .
text: acute salpingitis is a type of salpingitis.
Oophoritis is a type of ovarian disease, defined as an ovarian disease characterized by inflammation of the ovary.
Membranous glomerulonephritis is a type of glomerulonephritis and has an exact synonym, membranous nephropathy.

Fetal erythroblastosis is a type of microcytic anemia and has several exact synonyms. These include EF - Erythroblastosis foetalis, Haemolytic disease due to rhesus isoimmunisation, erythroblastosis fetalis, and rhesus isoimmunisation of the newborn.

Alport syndrome is a type of monogenic disease and is also a type of syndrome, indicating that it is something that at least has its basis in some gene. It is defined as a syndrome disease characterized by glomerulonephritis, end-stage kidney disease, and hearing loss. Furthermore, Alport syndrome has the exact synonym "Hereditary Nephritis."

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:discitis rdfs:subClassOf :cartilage_disease .
text: discitis is a type of cartilage disease.
Conjunctival vascular disease is a type of conjunctival disease and has exact synonyms: Conjunctival vascular abnormality and vascular abnormalities of conjunctiva.
Alpha thalassemia is a type of thalassemia, which involves the genes HBA1 and HBA2 hemoglobin genes. It is also exactly synonymous with Alpha thalassaemia and alpha-Thalassemia.

Basal ganglia cerebrovascular disease is defined as the intersection of conditions that are categorized under cerebrovascular disease and disorders that are located within the collection of basal ganglia. Furthermore, it is a specific type of cerebrovascular disease. Additionally, basal ganglia cerebrovascular disease has an exact match with the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) identifier D020144.

Acute hemorrhagic leukoencephalitis (AHL), also known as Weston-Hurst syndrome, acute haemorrhagic leucoencephalitis of Weston Hurst, acute hemorrhagic encephalomyelitis, and acute necrotizing hemorrhagic leukoencephalitis, is a type of acute disseminated encephalomyelitis and something that at least has the symptom of some hemorrhage. It is defined as a very rare form of acute disseminated encephalomyelitis, characterized by a brief but intense attack of inflammation and necrotizing vasculitis of venules and hemorrhage, and edema.

Postinfectious encephalitis is a type of autoimmune disease of the central nervous system and a subtype of encephalitis. It is also a type of condition that, at a minimum, exhibits the phenotype of abnormal immunoglobulin levels. Postinfectious encephalitis is characterized by the immune system mistakenly attacking healthy cells in the brain instead of only targeting the cells causing the infection; this often occurs two to three weeks after the initial infection. Additionally, postinfectious encephalitis is exactly synonymous with postinfective encephalitis and secondary encephalitis.

An immature cataract is a type of senile cataract and is defined as a senile cataract characterized by variable opacification of the lens of the eye, with some clear lens fibers still remaining. It is exactly synonymous with incipient cataract, incipient senile cataract, and water clefts.

Lens disease, a type of eye disease, is defined as an eye disease that affects the lens of the eye. This is significant as the lens is the transparent disc that focuses light onto the photosensors located at the back of the eye.

Ovarian disease is defined as a female reproductive system disease that is located in the ovary. It is equivalent to diseases that intersect with those having a location in the ovary and those that are at least characterized by disease. Ovarian disease is categorized as a type of gonadal disease, a type of female reproductive system disease, and also as a type of disease that has at least one symptom of inflammation.
Anorectal stricture is a type of anus disease and is also exactly known as Stenosis of rectum and anus.

text: pseudopterygium is a type of corneal disease.

Corneal edema is a type of corneal disease and is exactly synonymous with Corneal oedema.

:contact_lens_corneal_edema rdfs:subClassOf :corneal_edema .
text: contact lens corneal edema is a type of corneal edema.
Chronic rapidly progressive glomerulonephritis is a type of glomerulonephritis, and it is exactly synonymous with chronic glomerulonephritis with lesion of rapidly progressive glomerulonephritis.

Dissociative amnesia is a type of dissociative disorder defined as a condition where the continuity of the patient's memory is disrupted. In this disorder, patients experience recurrent episodes in which they forget important personal information or events, usually connected with trauma or severe stress. Additionally, dissociative amnesia is exactly synonymous with psychogenic amnesia.

Depersonalization disorder is a type of dissociative disorder characterized by persistent or recurrent feelings of depersonalization and/or derealization. It is also known by the exact synonym "Neurotic derealization."

Felty's syndrome is a type of syndrome and an autoimmune disease that at least has a phenotype with some abnormal immunoglobulin level. It is defined as a syndrome that results in rheumatoid arthritis, splenomegaly, and neutropenia. Felty's syndrome is also exactly synonymous with Felty syndrome and Rheumatoid arthritis with splenoadenomegaly and leukopenia.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:gastroschisis rdfs:subClassOf :physical_disorder .
text: gastroschisis is a type of physical disorder.

Meconium aspiration syndrome is a type of lung disease characterized by a newborn breathing in a mixture of meconium and amniotic fluid into the lungs around the time of delivery. This condition is also precisely referred to as Neonatal aspiration of meconium and meconium aspiration.

Urinary bladder cancer is identical to an entity that is both a cancer and a disease, specifically located in the urinary bladder. It is classified as a type of bladder disease as well as a type of urinary system cancer. This condition is defined as a cancer of the urinary system that results in malignant growth located in the urinary bladder. Furthermore, urinary bladder cancer is exactly synonymous with bladder cancer and tumor of the bladder.

Pasteurellosis, also known as Pasteurella infection or Pasteurella infectious disease, is a primary bacterial infectious disease. It results in systemic infection and has its material basis in Pasteurella multocida. The disease is transmitted through animal bites, scratches, or licks, and contact transmission. Symptoms of pasteurellosis include joint pain, tachycardia, fever, and it also features pneumonia as a disease characteristic. Additionally, the infection may present with rigors and meningeal irritation.

Esophagus lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and a type of esophageal cancer. It is also classified as a type of condition that has a material basis in some lymphocytes. Additionally, esophagus lymphoma is exactly synonymous with Lymphoma of esophagus, Lymphoma of oesophagus, and oesophagus lymphoma.
Placenta praevia is a type of placenta disease characterized by the attachment of the placenta to the uterine wall close to or covering the cervix.

Esophageal carcinoma is a type of carcinoma and also a type of esophageal cancer, which falls under a category that intersects with cancers and conditions deriving from epithelial cells. It is defined as an esophageal cancer characterized by abnormally proliferating cells that originate from epithelial cells. Furthermore, esophageal carcinoma is exactly synonymous with cancer of the esophagus, cancer of the oesophagus, carcinoma of the esophagus, and carcinoma of the oesophagus.

Brucella suis brucellosis is a type of brucellosis that involves an infection caused by Brucella suis in both swine and humans. This condition is characterized by several symptoms including fever, chills, malaise, diaphoresis, joint pain, headache, anorexia, and fatigue. Moreover, it is described as having a material basis in Brucella suis and exhibits a phenotype of hyperhidrosis.

Brucellosis is a primary bacterial infectious disease caused by bacteria of the genus Brucella. It is transmitted through contact transmission and vehicle-borne ingestion transmission. This disease has various symptoms, including backache, joint pain, weakness, headache, fever, and fatigue. The detailed definition of brucellosis highlights its transmission through contact with contaminated animals or animal products and ingestion of infected food products, further elaborating on symptoms like fever, sweat, headache, back pain, physical weakness, joint pain, and fatigue. 

Moreover, brucellosis is also known by several synonyms. It has exact synonyms such as Maltese fever and undulant fever. Additionally, it has related synonyms including Bang's disease, Gibraltar fever, Malta fever, and Mediterranean fever, indicating the various regional names and common terms associated with this infectious disease.

Leech infestation is defined as a parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that involves parasitic infestation by members of the subclass Hirudinea. During this process, leeches remain attached to their hosts, feeding on blood until they are full, after which they detach to digest. While feeding, leeches release an anesthetic and use a mix of mucus and suction to stay attached, besides secreting an anti-clotting enzyme, hirudin, into the host's bloodstream. It is also exactly synonymous with Hirudiniasis and Leeches.
Esophagus melanoma is a type of esophageal cancer, which has exact synonyms including melanoma of esophagus, melanoma of oesophagus, and oesophagus melanoma.

Myiasis is a type of parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease, which is defined as a parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that is caused by parasitic dipterous fly larvae (maggots) feeding on the host's necrotic or living tissue. It is exactly synonymous with infestation by fly larvae, infestation by maggots, and maggot infestation.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chorioretinal_scar rdfs:subClassOf :retinal_disease .
text: chorioretinal scar is a type of retinal disease.

Asphyxia neonatorum is a type of respiratory system disease characterized by the deprivation of oxygen to a newborn infant that lasts long enough during the birth process to cause physical harm, usually to the brain. It is alternatively known exactly as Asphyxia - birth, Asphyxia, in liveborn infant, Birth asphyxia, and postnatal asphyxia. Furthermore, asphyxia neonatorum is exactly matched with MESH:D001238 in medical databases.

Q fever is a primary bacterial infectious disease, also known precisely as an infection due to Coxiella burnetii. It is a zoonotic infectious disease that affects multiple organs and has a material basis in Coxiella burnetii. The transmission of Q fever occurs through various means, including inhalation of air contaminated by barnyard dust containing dried placental material, birth fluids, or excreta of infected herd animals, ingestion of contaminated milk, tick bites, and contact with an infected person. Additionally, Q fever can be transmitted through contact, airborne, vehicle-borne ingestion, and tick-borne methods. Symptoms of Q fever include fever, headache, cough, pleuritic chest pain, joint pain (arthralgia), and myalgia.

Trench fever, also known exactly as His-Werner disease, Quintan fever, Wolhynian fever, shin bone fever, and tibialgic fever, is a type of bartonellosis and is characterized by systemic infection. The disease has its material basis in Bartonella quintana, which is transmitted by body lice (Pediculus humanus corporis). It is defined as a primary bacterial infectious disease featuring symptoms such as relapsing fever, headache, shin pain, and soreness of the muscles of the legs and back. Moreover, trench fever has an exact match in the medical subject headings (MESH) with the identifier D014205.

Bartonellosis is a type of primary bacterial infectious disease, which has the definition of a primary bacterial infectious disease that is caused by the bacteria of the genus Bartonella. It has exact synonyms including Bartonella infectious disease, Rochalimaea infection, and bartonelliasis.

Rickettsialpox is a type of spotted fever and is also known as Rickettsia akari spotted fever or Vesicular rickettsiosis. It has a material basis in Rickettsia akari and is transmitted by insect-borne transmission, specifically by the house mouse mite (Liponyssoides sanguineus) found on mice and other rodents. The symptoms of rickettsialpox include fever, chills, headache, myalgia, and a papulovesicular rash.

Spotted fever is defined as a primary bacterial infectious disease that results in infection located in the endothelial cell of an artery or in the endothelial cell of a vein. It has a material basis in Rickettsia and is transmitted by ticks and mites. The symptoms of spotted fever include fever, headache, fatigue, muscle aches, and a maculopapular or petechial rash. In some cases, a distinctive eschar may develop at the site of a tick bite. This disease is also known as the Spotted fever group rickettsial disease. It is transmitted by entities that are either insect-borne or tick-borne. The symptoms of spotted fever also include a maculopapular rash.

Fundus albipunctatus is a type of fundus dystrophy characterized by discrete uniform white dots over the entire fundus with greatest density in the midperiphery and no macular involvement. It also has the exact synonyms Pigmentary retinal dystrophy and retinitis punctata albescens.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:hydronephrosis rdfs:subClassOf :urinary_tract_obstruction .
text: hydronephrosis is a type of urinary tract obstruction.

Gilles de la Tourette syndrome is a type of tic disorder that is characterized by multiple physical (motor) tics and at least one vocal (phonic) tic which are present for more than a year. This syndrome is also known by the exact synonyms Guinon's disease, Psychogenic tics, Tourette syndrome, and motor-verbal tic disorder, indicating its various aspects and interpretations in medical terminology.
Psychologic dyspareunia is a type of psychosexual disorder, which is exactly synonymous with both Dyspareunia, psychogenic and Non-organic dyspareunia.
Pulpitis is a type of dental pulp disease characterized by inflammation and has an exact synonym, pulp stones.

Henoch-Schoenlein purpura is a type of hypersensitivity vasculitis characterized by purpura (purplish plaques), arthralgia, gastrointestinal upset, and/or glomerulonephritis. It may be related to an increased immune response following an infection. This condition is also exactly synonymous with several terms, including Allergic purpura, Autoimmune purpura, Henoch-Schnlein purpura, Henoch-Schnlein purpura, Henoch-Scholein purpura, Henoch-Schonlein Purpura, and Purpura, autoimmune.
A qualitative platelet defect is a type of blood platelet disease, which is also precisely known as qualitative platelet deficiency.
Acquired thrombocytopenia is a type of thrombocytopenia, which is exactly synonymous with secondary thrombocytopenia.
